<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8" />
    <!-- stuff for pdf generation -->
    <meta name="author" content="BastionLedger http://www.last-bastion.net/forge/bastionledger"/>
    <meta name="subject" content="" tal:attributes="content context/Title"/>
    <title tal:content="context/title_or_id"/>
    <style tal:replace="structure context/blemail.css"/>
  </head>
  <body class="body" tal:define="share options/share;
                                 effective options/effective;
                                 quantity options/quantity;
                                 newline_to_br python: modules['Products.PythonScripts.standard'].newline_to_br">

      <h3 align="center" tal:content="python: context.getLedgerProperty('title')" />
      <h3 align="center"><tal:address tal:content="structure python: newline_to_br(context.getLedgerProperty('address'))" /></h3>

      <h4 align="center">
         <i>Company No. <span tal:replace="python: context.getLedgerProperty('company_number')"/></i>
      </h4>

      <h2 align="center">Share Certificate - <span tal:replace="share/Title"/></h2>
 
      <div class="label" tal:content="context/Title"/>
      <div tal:content="structure python: newline_to_br(context.address)" />

      <p>This is to cerify that as at <span tal:replace="python: context.toLocalizedTime(effective)"/>, 
         <span tal:replace="context/Title"/> is the registered holder of <span tal:replace="quantity"/> 
         <span tal:replace="share/Title"/> shares of <span tal:replace="share/face"/> each in 
         <span tal:replace="python: context.getLedgerProperty('title')"/>.</p>

      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <hr/>
      <div style="font-size: 8pt; font-style:italic">
          Powered by <a href="http://www.last-bastion.net/forge/BastionLedger">BastionLedger</a>
      </div>

  </body>
</html>
